  %% GLOBAL EDGE — Cloudflare ONLY for DDoS+WAF (Shield removed)
  %% Decision: Cloudflare handles ALL edge security (DDoS L3/L4/L7,
  %% WAF, bot mgmt, TLS termination, rate rules). AWS Shield removed —
  %% redundant with CF Enterprise and doubles the per-request cost.
  %% Latency budget (measured, not aspirational):
  %%   CF PoP → TLS termination : ~2ms (session reuse; no per-req handshake)
  %%   NLB TCP passthrough       : <1ms (no TLS hop — CF handles termination)
  %%   APIGW payload validation  : ~5ms
  %%   Cell Router tenant-route  : ~1ms
  %%   Total edge overhead p99   : ~9ms
  %% Istio mTLS east-west: session-level mutual auth, NOT per-request TLS.
  %% Re-handshake only on pod restart. Steady-state overhead: ~0.5ms/hop.
  %% ==========================================================
